{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1769468783,"nonce":"T+fMf5pIiIg2PDpOjpqXHu6thPQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87l9S4wzwAAAAUxUlqV"},"added":["documentation"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1769468783,"nonce":"fBT0GqCDPHGna61k/u89nW6GTxI=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87l9S4wzwAAAAUxUlrM"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1769531958,"nonce":"qVi2+hD2k4NGwACwiMGGv/cuemY=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87i3pNd","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/46#issuecomment-3806237533"},"message":"**Broadening Scope: AI CLI Interoperability (Gemini + Copilot)**\n\nI strongly support improving the CLI onboarding! As I'm working with Gemini CLI, I see identical gaps. I propose we structure this to be \"AI CLI agnostic\" where possible to minimize maintenance and fill gaps for both platforms.\n\n**Suggestions:**\n\n1.  **Unified Quickstart (`.agent/AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md`)**:\n    Instead of a Copilot-exclusive guide, create a shared CLI quickstart. It can cover the universal steps (sourcing env, git identity) and have brief subsections for tool-specifics (Copilot `gh copilot suggest` vs Gemini).\n\n2.  **De-duplicate Instructions**:\n    `.github/copilot-instructions.md` currently repeats the list of \"Essential Documentation\" found in `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md`.\n    *   **Proposal**: Move the core \"Rules of Engagement\" (Read these 5 files, usage of `status_report.sh`, etc.) to a single `.agent/AI_RULES.md`.\n    *   **Ref**: Update `copilot-instructions.md` (and any future Gemini context) to simply link to `AI_RULES.md` as the authoritative source.\n\n3.  **Smarter Identity Script**:\n    Enhance `.agent/scripts/configure_git_identity.sh` to support a profile flag (e.g., `--agent gemini` or `--agent copilot`) to auto-fill the correct email/name conventions, removing the need for users to remember the specific identity strings.\n\n4.  **Universal Command Mapping**:\n    For the \"Slash Commands\" (Point 3 in the issue), if we define mappings (e.g., `/build` -\u003e `colcon build`), let's document them in a way that works for any agent to read and execute, possibly as a simple `COMMANDS.md` or a set of shell aliases we can ask any agent to \"load\".\n\nThis approach solves the immediate Copilot gap while \"future-proofing\" for Gemini or other local LLM agents without extra overhead.\n\n**🤖 Authored-By**: Gemini CLI Agent","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1769541852,"nonce":"B1qdnWIr/+hx9YMV0JNAfh7UVAg=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87l9S4wzwAAAAUyxAQ7"},"status":2}]}